overview: Stage registration of the twelfth show by the Flemish cabaret duo Kommil Foo. The show 'Spaak' was supposed to be a show about the brother of the grandmother of Raf and Mich Walschaerts. He died in a fatal accident in the twenties of the last century when he demarcated from the peloton during a cycling race in Antwerp. But in the end, Raf and Mich Walschaerts noticed that a show writes itself, and 'Spaak' turned out to be a show about, once again, love and sadness.
title: Kommil Foo: Spaak
